items.jobDescribe:
Main Tasks:
HRBP
- Support the implementation of HR solutions from the global/regional HR framework and, if applicable, bring in local perspectives and develop customized HR initiatives for the assigned site/unit.
- Provide implementation support on organization design, restructuring and cultural change for the assigned site/unit in alignment with business leaders and HR leadership. Responsible for HR project management and related communication in the assigned area.
- Facilitate site/unit's talent development based on business and operational needs, including related discussions (e.g. succession planning, talent review/forum), support unit’s candidate management. Discuss with site/unit leaders to identify training needs and, if applicable, demand for customized solutions.
- Co-work with line managers and recruiters to fulfill recruitment requests in an effective and efficient approach. Handle exit interviews, analyze the employee separation reason and turnover statistics and provide useful information/data to improve employee retention. Facilitate and enable internal transfers, promotions and relocations etc., to serve business needs. Draft personnel announcements when needed.
- Implement Global/Regional programs and initiate local programs in employee relationship, e.g., Employee Voices, employee communications etc., to enhance employee satisfaction and promote company culture.
Requirements:
- Bachelor degree or above, major in human resources or psychology is preferred;
- Minimum 5 to 7 years of experience in HR full functions in MNC; familiar with China labor law/regulations;
- Fluent in English, proficient MS Office applications;
- Able to work independently, take initiative, set and execute work plans, effective communication and team collaboration spirits;
- Strong business affinity and acumen, experience working with senior management and ability to operate and influence with impact in a matrix environment;
- Entrepreneurial and customer focus with strong drive to successfully steer HR solutions in the region.
